Round 1:
[Patient] Can you recommend exercises that are safe for me to do in my neighborhood?
[Healthcare Educator] Walking or cycling on safe streets can be good options for you.

Round 2:
[Patient] I want to start being more active, but I'm worried about overdoing it.
[Healthcare Educator] Start slow and gradually increase intensity to avoid straining your heart.

Round 3:
[Patient] Are there any specific exercises I should avoid due to my heart condition?
[Healthcare Educator] Avoid heavy weightlifting or high-intensity interval training to prevent excessive strain.

Round 4:
[Patient] Can I still participate in group fitness classes at the gym?
[Healthcare Educator] Yes, low-impact classes like yoga or water aerobics may be beneficial for you.

Round 5:
[Patient] How often should I exercise to help improve my heart health?
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate exercise most days of the week.